body:
I saw Endgame last night

I’m emotionally destroyed.

An entire era has definetly came to an end now.

Even if i do not totally accept Russo’s choices over some characters (Steve’s and Tony’s first of all), Endgame is really the best movie of its genre i’ve ever seen.

I’ll always love Tony, Steve, Thor, Natasha, Clint, Bruce 3000.

Now it’s time to move on.

body:
Avengers endgame

Let’s talk about Clint Barton.

SPOILERS ALLERT

…

Do not read further if you do not want to spoil the movie.

…

SPOILERS

…

Well, you’ve been warned .

…

Clint : the development of a broken man.

Clint lost a lot.

he lost his family, he lost his wife, his kids. He lost himself.

His way of coping with the aftermath of infinity war, it was so real, you can totally relate.

He shows us how the lost, the loneliness, the sadness can change you. He shows us that being a super hero doesn’t make you invincible.

He showed us his humanity.

It’s not a movie where everyone says “ok, I’m not hurt with the all situation, let’s move on”.

This movie showed that sometimes it’s just hard.

Sometimes it’s just too much.

And that’s ok, that’s what makes us humans.

That shows us that we have feelings, we can be lost, we can be vulnerable, because we are not machines.

It showed us how you need to collect your shit, and deal with It.

However long it takes.

Whatever it takes.

It showed us how you can be in a hard situation, where everything feels a lost cause, everything feels empty, dead, dark, but you need to stand up, be strong , deal with it and do the right thing.

In my opinion that was so interesting to watch.

What do you think about it?
